8:05 - Not sure about it, will watch it again, will rate later...
Denial is the first stage... You will watch it again and see the pile of shit most of the people say it is. Just like The Last Jedi was for most of us.
But don't tell people to 'go watch it' when you are unsure of how to react and cautious about giving a rating.
If it's a bad movie, people shouldn't "go watch it" just because they follow the franchise. People should realize the power of voting with your wallet.

snippet.textDisplay:
No, the Prequels were awful, the original trilogy still rocks. The sequels got off to a good start, the last Jedi isn’t as bad as some of the keyboard warriors rant it is, but already, there’s some really angry toxic man babies, going after Rise of Skywalker with some real venom.
I was 8 when Star Wars came out, loved all 3 movies, but The Phantom Menace left me so cold I refused to watch any of the subsequent episodes, only with The Force Awakens did I feel any love again for the franchise, (with my son who is a similar age as I was when I first saw Star Wars,) and I’ve enjoyed every instalment since in the universe, the grittiness of Rogue One, and Solo, I’ve watched 3 or 4 times, and it’s a solid effort, again, I don’t understand the complaints!
Off to see ROS over Xmas, which seems to be the tradition of the past 4 years it seems! If I’m honest, I’ve enjoyed the SW universe films, more than the main films themselves, Mandalorian has also been very entertaining, and in my opinion, the extended SW universe offers greater opportunities, and should bare plenty of fruit

snippet.textDisplay: The Continuity of thought of episodes 1-7 suffer in TROS because of TLJ.  George Lucas started with episode 4 because there as no way at the time to make 1-3 as live action films. He created the story using common archetypes and religious light versus dark overtones and created something terrific.  He also created Industrial Light and Magic to give us dinosaurs, transforming robots and comic book heroes. He is a genius that worked with other brilliant members of industry to create many iconic things, but it all happened with Continuity of Thought.  The Marvel pictures set the bar so high when 20+ movies wove together because of love of the project and continuity of thought. In these Star Wars films a tortured family influences and inspires to nurture hope in where worlds of people fight for the greater good. At the basic level as foster/surrogate parents Luke and Leah made Rey a Skywalker through Nurture. But hopefully Rey is carrying a Skywalker as through Anakin's same immaculate conception.
